TY  - JOUR
AU  - Gordon, Roger H.
T1  - An Optimal Taxation Approach to Fiscal Federalism*
PY  - 1983
Y1  - 1983/11/01
DO  - 10.2307/1881778
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 98
IS  - 4
SP  - 567
EP  - 586
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - In a Federal system of government, each unit of government decides independently how much of each type of public good to provide, and what types of taxes, and which tax rates, to use in funding the public goods. In this paper we explore what types of problems can arise from this decentralized form of decision-making. In particular, we describe systematically the types of externalities that one unit of government can create for nonresidents, through both its public goods decisions and its taxation decisions. The paper also explores briefly what the central government might do to lessen the costs of decentralized decision-making.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/1881778
ER  - 



